'''Kjersti Fløttum''' (born 12 July 1953) is a Norwegian linguist.
After a tenure at [[Stavanger University College]] she was hired at the [[University of Bergen]] in 1995 where she is a professor of [[French language]]. She has been a vice rector of international relations and from 2007 to 2011 led the Bergen Summer Research School.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jubilant|work=Bergens Tidende|date=12 July 2013|language=Norwegian}}</ref>
Fløttum is also [[consul (representative)|vice-consul]] for France in [[Bergen]], and active in the [[Rafto Foundation]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Jubilant|work=Bergens Tidende|date=11 July 2013|author=Alvsåker, Anders|author2=Didriksen, Øyvind|author3=Gjerstad, Anje|author4=Gjesdal, Müller|author5=Thue Vold, Eva|language=Norwegian}}</ref>
