'''Misha Kokaia''' (Georgian: მიშა კოკაია) (born 1954) is a [[Georgia (country)|Georgian]] politician and Doctor of Mathematics who was last seen on  27 September 1993.

==Disappearance==
The last time Kokaia was seen was 27 September 1993, when the city of [[Sukhumi]] fell to the Russian-supported separatist forces. Some say that he was killed in Sukhumi along with [[Zhiuli Shartava]], [[Guram Gabiskiria]] and others by Abkhaz separatist rebels during the ethnic cleaning of Georgians in Abkhazia on the same date.

